A valid reason for terminating a tenancy after the first 6 months includes:
- Not adhering to the terms of the lease agreement (i.e breach of contract);
- Causing significant damage or nuisance to the premises;
- Using the property for illegal activities;
- Failing to pay rent or other charges on time and consistently. In some cases, Landlords may also terminate a tenancy due to wishing to occupy the property themselves, selling it, or carrying out repairs and improvements which would require vacant possession. Always check the specific landlord-tenant laws in your jurisdiction to determine the legal grounds for termination.

